headline: Kimberly-Clark (NASDAQ:KMB) Reports Q3 In Line With Expectations
summary: Household products company Kimberly-Clark (NYSE:KMB) met Wall Streets revenue expectations in Q3 CY2025, but sales were flat year on year at $4.15 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $1.82 per share was 3.9% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
